<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="470" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,577,964]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,577,603]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the smallest of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[567,690,578,603]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[567,690,578,603]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with body lengths of about 
<quantity box="[1091,1170,577,604]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="28.0">28 mm</quantity>
and a wing span of less than 
<quantity box="[208,291,613,640]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="80.0">80 mm</quantity>
. The generic characters will distinguish it from other known 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1092,613,639]" name="Suriname" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Suriname</collectingCountry>
cicadas but additional species of the genus will probably be found in the future. The species has a green head and thorax marked with piceous, a piceous abdomen, the postclypeus does not extend anteriorly beyond the supra-antennal plates when viewed from the dorsal side, and the fore wing radial and radiomedial crossveins lack infuscation. These characteristics can be used to distinguish it from other 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[517,640,758,783]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[517,640,758,783]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species that may be found in 
<collectingCountry box="[974,1081,757,783]" name="Suriname" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Suriname</collectingCountry>
eventually.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="470" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,577,964]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,793,819]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species has previously been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[882,953,793,819]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[963,1087,793,819]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1097,1192,793,819]" name="Ecuador" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1203,1370,793,819]" name="French Guiana" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Guatemala" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[239,351,829,855]" name="Honduras" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Honduras</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[361,479,829,855]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[535,624,830,856]" name="Panama" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[637,804,829,855]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref20456" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[815,985,829,855]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" pagination="377 - 418" refId="ref21244" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2011 a) Checklist of the cicadas of French Guiana including new records and the description of nine new species (Insecta, Hemiptera, Cicadoidea, Cicadidae). Zoosystema, 33, 377 - 418. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2011 n 3 a 6" type="journal article" year="2011">Sanborn 2011a</bibRefCitation>
; 2013; 2014a; 2018b; 2020d; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Maes, J. - M." pageId="17" pageNumber="470" pagination="437 - 442" refId="ref22668" refString="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Maes, J. - M. (2012) Checklist of the cicadas (Insecta: Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Nicaragua including new re- cords for seventeen species. Check List, 8, 437 - 442. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 8.3.437" type="journal article" year="2012">Sanborn &amp; Maes 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Maes, J. - M. &amp; Moulds, M. &amp; Sanborn, A. F." box="[290,481,865,892]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref19818" refString="Maes, J. - M., Moulds, M. &amp; Sanborn, A. F. (2012) Cicadidae (Homoptera) de Nicaragua: catalogo ilustrado, incluyendo especies exoticas del Museo Entomologico de Leon. Revista Nicaraguense Entomologia, 72 (Suplemento 2), 1 - 138." type="journal article" year="2012">
Maes 
<emphasis box="[357,414,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). The range was expanded recently to include 
<collectingCountry box="[999,1050,866,892]" name="Peru" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[1065,1240,865,891]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" pagination="1 - 129" refId="ref22283" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2020 c) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Peru including the descriptions of twenty-four new species, three new synonymies, and thirty-seven new records. Zootaxa, 4785 (1), 1 - 129. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4785.1.1" type="journal article" year="2020">Sanborn 2020c</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
